- Don&#39;t extend `JFrame`.
- Do extend `JPanel` and use that to hold components, etc.
- Also note that you do not need to make all the classes public. Only the one that contains the `static main` entry point is required.  For small programs like this, just add classes without any access level modifiers (public, private,etc) right after the main public class.  It can make it easier to debug and modify.  The down side is for large programs, you will needlessly compile everything.   In that case use separate class files.

